00:17:08,087 --> 00:17:09,477
Did she commit a grave sin or something?

259
00:17:09,477 --> 00:17:12,637
Do they think they're so above it all?

260
00:17:12,637 --> 00:17:17,067
Mom, you can't just do that.

261
00:17:19,037 --> 00:17:20,737
You little bastard!

262
00:17:20,737 --> 00:17:23,817
We saved you from going to jail. What did you say just now?

263
00:17:23,817 --> 00:17:26,817
Gosh, there's no point in having a son!

264
00:17:26,817 --> 00:17:31,107
How could he not understand how I feel? How could he?

265
00:17:31,107 --> 00:17:33,227
Gosh, seriously!

266
00:17:36,407 --> 00:17:38,637
 Having hobbies would be great. 

267
00:17:38,637 --> 00:17:42,517
 Seeing someone else would help, too. 

268
00:17:42,517 --> 00:17:45,877
 I'll prescribe you medicine. Make sure to take it, too. 

269
00:17:49,227 --> 00:17:52,987
Fine, I'll take the medicine.

270
00:17:52,987 --> 00:17:55,807
He must be an expert for a reason.

271
00:17:56,497 --> 00:17:58,287
Park Do Ra is dead.

272
00:17:58,287 --> 00:18:01,617
But I keep thinking the country bumpkin is her.

273
00:18:01,617 --> 00:18:06,197
It's just an illusion created by my weak heart.

274
00:18:07,097 --> 00:18:09,927
I'll take the medicine and fix it.

275
00:18:27,297 --> 00:18:29,017
   

276
00:18:39,957 --> 00:18:42,327
Yes, Tae Hee.

277
00:19:58,067 --> 00:20:02,197
What did you want to tell me urgently?

278
00:20:06,277 --> 00:20:08,667
I got fired, right?

279
00:20:09,227 --> 00:20:12,187
You wanted to tell me that, right?

280
00:20:17,127 --> 00:20:19,657
Of course, I got fired.

281
00:20:19,657 --> 00:20:21,977
I have to perform at the nightclub nine more times.

282
00:20:21,977 --> 00:20:23,957
How could they work with me?

283
00:20:23,957 --> 00:20:26,907
No, you didn't get fired.

284
00:20:29,497 --> 00:20:31,387
Stop teasing me.

285
00:20:31,387 --> 00:20:39,717
I know President Jang and Writer wanted me fired since they couldn't allow me to perform at the nightclub.

286
00:20:40,597 --> 00:20:45,407
Ji Yeong, Director Go took care of all that.

287
00:20:45,407 --> 00:20:46,837
Pardon?

288
00:20:47,377 --> 00:20:49,757
Director Go did? How?

289
00:20:49,757 --> 00:20:53,837
I managed to put together 10 million won

290
00:20:53,837 --> 00:20:57,167
and went to the nightclub to cancel your contract.

291
00:20:57,167 --> 00:21:02,547
But they said your contract was canceled, and the penalty was paid, too.

292
00:21:03,247 --> 00:21:05,677
W-What are you talking about?

293
00:21:05,677 --> 00:21:10,267
Director Go went to the nightclub and even paid the penalty.

294
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:12,067
- What? 
 - And...

295
00:21:12,067 --> 00:21:15,617
President Jang and Writer kept insisting on replacing you,

296
00:21:15,617 --> 00:21:18,737
but Director Go said he'd work with you

297
00:21:18,737 --> 00:21:22,887
and he'd be responsible until the end.

298
00:21:23,847 --> 00:21:25,757
Is that true?

299
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:27,547
Yes.

300
00:21:27,547 --> 00:21:31,527
Ji Yeong, we really need to work hard from now on.

301
00:21:31,527 --> 00:21:35,047
That's how we'd return the favor to him. You know what I mean?

302
00:21:35,047 --> 00:21:37,267
You would've gotten fired immediately if it wasn't for him.

303
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:39,867
But he saved us.

304
00:21:39,867 --> 00:21:44,747
Director Go must care about you a lot.

305
00:21:44,747 --> 00:21:47,107
Director Go?

306
00:21:59,517 --> 00:22:04,837
 Hello, Director. Can we meet right now? 

307
00:22:11,643 --> 00:22:16,253
Director, thank you.

308
00:22:16,253 --> 00:22:19,673
President Lee told me everything.

309
00:22:19,673 --> 00:22:22,443
I should've gotten fired,

310
00:22:22,443 --> 00:22:26,903
but you paid the penalty for me

311
00:22:26,903 --> 00:22:33,053
and you told Writer and President Jang that you'd be responsible for me.

312
00:22:34,023 --> 00:22:36,873
Thank you so much.

313
00:22:36,873 --> 00:22:42,293
And I'm so sorry I caused trouble.

314
00:22:44,343 --> 00:22:48,233
Work hard and return the favor with good acting.

315
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:51,263
Okay. I really will work hard.

316
00:22:51,263 --> 00:22:55,043
I'll do the best I can. But...

317
00:22:58,203 --> 00:23:03,923
I can't pay you back right now.

318
00:23:06,283 --> 00:23:11,073
I'll pay you back as soon as I get the contract money.

319
00:23:11,073 --> 00:23:14,343
Please wait until then.

320
00:23:16,193 --> 00:23:18,053
Take your time with that.

321
00:23:19,643 --> 00:23:21,703
And Ji Yeong,

322
00:23:22,503 --> 00:23:25,933
we said you made a mistake since you're inexperienced,

323
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:29,713
but if you do this again, it'd no longer be a mistake.

324
00:23:29,713 --> 00:23:33,663
All the efforts you've made might get ruined then.

325
00:23:33,663 --> 00:23:35,963
Yes, I'll make sure this never happens again.

326
00:23:35,963 --> 00:23:38,163
I swear I won't allow it.

327
00:23:38,163 --> 00:23:43,853
Okay. Put everything in the past and solely focus on acting now.

328
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,183
Okay.

329
00:23:47,563 --> 00:23:54,803
The writer gave in at the last minute because we really need you on our drama.

330
00:23:54,803 --> 00:23:59,223
So, don't be so discouraged from this.

331
00:23:59,923 --> 00:24:01,513
Okay.

332
00:24:10,683 --> 00:24:12,873
Director,

333
00:24:15,403 --> 00:24:19,723
you're being so generous to me.

334
00:24:19,723 --> 00:24:23,413
I really don't know what to do.

335
00:24:23,413 --> 00:24:26,753
Don't feel pressured, Ji Yeong.

336
00:24:26,753 --> 00:24:31,893
I promised you that I'll always help you whenever you face hardship.

337
00:24:31,893 --> 00:24:34,373
That I'll always protect you.

338
00:24:34,373 --> 00:24:38,563
So, talk to me first if you face any trouble.

339
00:24:39,343 --> 00:24:46,643
Ji Yeong, do you know why I'm just waiting for you instead of approaching you?

340
00:24:46,643 --> 00:24:48,433
Pardon?

341
00:24:48,433 --> 00:24:50,853
You must be confused enough right now.

342
00:24:50,853 --> 00:24:53,623
I don't want to add to your stress.

343
00:24:53,623 --> 00:24:56,743
Until you understand, accept the situation,

344
00:24:56,743 --> 00:25:01,353
and get settled, I'm giving it some time.

345
00:25:02,853 --> 00:25:07,323
You live with President Baek now, but if I kept approaching you,

346
00:25:07,323 --> 00:25:11,343
you'd feel more stressed between President Baek and me.

347
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:14,583
I don't want you to feel stressed.

348
00:25:15,693 --> 00:25:20,803
When you were Do Ra, you had a rough time because of President Baek.

349
00:25:20,803 --> 00:25:25,023
I'm sure President Baek read through your contract.

350
00:25:25,023 --> 00:25:29,163
She must've known performing at a nightclub was against the contract.

351
00:25:29,163 --> 00:25:32,523
But she still made you perform there.

352
00:25:32,523 --> 00:25:37,033
Do you think she would've done that if she cared about you?

353
00:25:39,843 --> 00:25:43,353
You had such a hard time because of this incident.

354
00:25:43,353 --> 00:25:49,113
President Baek did that to Do Ra, too. That's why I wanted you to move on from your past

355
00:25:49,113 --> 00:25:51,753
and live as Kim Ji Yeong.

356
00:25:52,363 --> 00:25:59,203
Director, I'm so thankful that you thought of me and cared for me.

357
00:25:59,203 --> 00:26:01,963
I can't thank you enough for that.

358
00:26:01,963 --> 00:26:08,023
But... please don't speak badly of my mom anymore.

359
00:26:08,023 --> 00:26:14,453
I'm just happy having a meal with my mom, older brother, and little brother.

360
00:26:14,453 --> 00:26:18,213
I have no money, and we can't all live together yet,

361
00:26:18,213 --> 00:26:21,303
but I'm happy I have a family.

362
00:26:25,103 --> 00:26:27,833
Okay, I understand.

363
00:26:37,473 --> 00:26:41,133
Here's a present to express my gratitude.

364
00:26:42,383 --> 00:26:44,983
I'll get going now.

365
00:27:11,173 --> 00:27:14,923
Why does my heart keep leaning toward the Director?

366
00:27:16,163 --> 00:27:20,543
Why do I keep having feelings for the man who criticizes my mom?

367
00:27:22,273 --> 00:27:24,403
No, Kim Ji Yeong.

368
00:27:24,403 --> 00:27:29,303
Director Go is a bad man who tried to separate a mother and child.

369
00:27:33,423 --> 00:27:35,393
But...

370
00:27:37,523 --> 00:27:41,143
I don't think he's a bad man.

371
00:27:42,543 --> 00:27:48,523
How could those moist and deer-like eyes belong to a bad man?

372
00:27:53,783 --> 00:27:56,383
What am I supposed to do now?

373
00:28:14,033 --> 00:28:17,243
Aigoo, Ji Yeong!

374
00:28:17,243 --> 00:28:19,503
I just got a call from Jae Dong.

375
00:28:19,503 --> 00:28:22,673
My gosh, I can't believe you didn't get fired.

376
00:28:22,673 --> 00:28:26,093
This is so wonderful.

377
00:28:26,093 --> 00:28:29,653
Wait just a moment. The potato and beef stew are almost done. Let's eat this

378
00:28:29,653 --> 00:28:35,313
and look for a salon to do your hair and makeup, okay?

379
00:28:36,183 --> 00:28:39,033
Excuse me, Ahjumma.

380
00:28:39,033 --> 00:28:40,583
Yes?

381
00:28:41,263 --> 00:28:43,283
Well...

382
00:28:44,173 --> 00:28:49,603
I keep thinking Director Go isn't a bad man.

383
00:28:49,603 --> 00:28:51,863
He paid the penalty for canceling the contract.

384
00:28:51,863 --> 00:28:56,093
The writer kept insisting on replacing me,

385
00:28:56,093 --> 00:29:02,703
but he said he'd take responsibility and helped me not get fired, apparently.

386
00:29:06,773 --> 00:29:10,023
The fact that he didn't tell me I was Park Do Ra

387
00:29:10,023 --> 00:29:16,053
and you were my mom because I think he really cares about me.

388
00:29:16,053 --> 00:29:20,053
Because he wanted me to live as Kim Ji Yeong, not Park Do Ra.

389
00:29:20,053 --> 00:29:25,593
Because I'd have a hard time if people found out I was Park Do Ra.

390
00:29:25,593 --> 00:29:29,453
So? What are you trying to say?

391
00:29:30,363 --> 00:29:34,733
I think I was too harsh on him.

392
00:29:34,733 --> 00:29:40,043
I don't think I should've been harsh to him and broke up with him.

393
00:29:40,773 --> 00:29:46,953
So... Are you saying you'll get back together with him?

394
00:29:46,953 --> 00:29:48,053
Pardon?

395
00:29:48,053 --> 00:29:50,873
Wake up, Kim Ji Yeong!

396
00:29:50,873 --> 00:29:53,673
You're still being tricked by that bastard like a fool.

397
00:29:53,673 --> 00:29:56,673
Why do you think he paid for your penalty?

398
00:29:56,673 --> 00:30:00,823
He's trying to use you with money. He's toying with your heart!

399
00:30:00,823 --> 00:30:03,963
Gosh, seriously.

400
00:30:03,963 --> 00:30:10,763
How could you get tempted by someone who tried to separate us?

401
00:30:10,763 --> 00:30:12,793
Don't you care about how I feel?

402
00:30:12,793 --> 00:30:14,803
Do you care about him more than me?

403
00:30:14,803 --> 00:30:17,143
N-No, it's not like that.

404
00:30:17,143 --> 00:30:19,193
Once you receive the contract money,

405
00:30:19,193 --> 00:30:23,143
we'll pay him back first. Stop with the silly thoughts, okay?

406
00:30:24,203 --> 00:30:25,493
Okay.

407
00:30:25,493 --> 00:30:29,433
Gosh. Gosh, seriously...

408
00:30:29,433 --> 00:30:32,063
Gosh, I'm so upset...

409
00:30:43,493 --> 00:30:46,173
Seon Yeong, have some porridge.

410
00:30:46,173 --> 00:30:47,873
You need to have a bite.

411
00:30:47,873 --> 00:30:50,973
It's bad for you if you don't eat anything.

412
00:30:53,313 --> 00:30:55,313
Mother,

413
00:30:56,313 --> 00:30:59,713
why have I been living so foolishly?

414
00:31:02,133 --> 00:31:05,773
I thought she was a good friend.

415
00:31:06,613 --> 00:31:09,543
I only felt grateful...

416
00:31:09,543 --> 00:31:13,813
and I wanted to return the favor.

417
00:31:15,473 --> 00:31:19,503
Why didn't I ever suspect it?

418
00:31:22,493 --> 00:31:26,583
Is there anyone as foolish as me?

419
00:31:28,463 --> 00:31:30,493
Seon Yeong,

420
00:31:30,493 --> 00:31:36,703
anyone can fall for it if a fraudster is determined to deceive to you.

421
00:31:36,703 --> 00:31:39,373
You know how good that bitch was to you.

422
00:31:39,373 --> 00:31:42,873
And she loved Pil Sung so much as a baby.

423
00:31:43,553 --> 00:31:46,503
It was because he was her baby.

424
00:31:46,503 --> 00:31:51,653
We just thanked her without suspecting anything.

425
00:31:53,843 --> 00:31:58,823
She abandoned her baby in someone else's nest like a cuckoo.

426
00:31:58,823 --> 00:32:02,673
Why are you a fool? She's the devious one.

427
00:32:02,673 --> 00:32:06,323
How could she be so terrible while pretending to be a human?

428
00:32:06,323 --> 00:32:09,043
Gosh, what a bitch.

429
00:32:11,083 --> 00:32:14,063
 Are you in there? It's Ma Ri! 

430
00:32:15,063 --> 00:32:18,053
Seon Yeong, stay in here.

431
00:32:18,053 --> 00:32:20,463
I'll send her back.

432
00:32:34,113 --> 00:32:39,073
Ma Ri, what are you doing here?

433
00:32:39,073 --> 00:32:41,213
Grandma, what happened?

434
00:32:41,213 --> 00:32:43,933
Why did you grab my mom's hair with Seon Yeong?

435
00:32:43,933 --> 00:32:50,723
Did you tell her all about our secret by chance?

436
00:32:50,723 --> 00:32:52,223
What?

437
00:32:54,933 --> 00:32:58,763
You promised me to keep it a secret!

438
00:32:58,763 --> 00:33:04,383
M-Ma Ri, I tried to keep it a secret at first, too.

439
00:33:04,383 --> 00:33:08,343
But you can't keep this a secret.

440
00:33:08,343 --> 00:33:12,123
Your mom committed a grave sin.

441
00:33:12,123 --> 00:33:15,023
That's why I couldn't keep it a secret.

442
00:33:15,023 --> 00:33:17,263
But you can't just do that.

443
00:33:17,263 --> 00:33:22,383
How could you pull my mom's hair like that?

444
00:33:23,283 --> 00:33:27,223
Young lady, I know she's your mom, but you can't defend her for that.

445
00:33:27,223 --> 00:33:30,283
How about us, whom she fooled all this time?

446
00:33:30,283 --> 00:33:33,583
Get out right now. And don't ever come back.

447
00:33:33,583 --> 00:33:37,643
I hate to see your whole family.

448
00:33:37,643 --> 00:33:41,053
Get out right now. Get out!

449
00:33:41,053 --> 00:33:42,543
I'm sorry.

450
00:33:42,543 --> 00:33:44,823
Ma Ri, Ma Ri... Seriously!

451
00:33:44,823 --> 00:33:46,773
Why would you say that to her? You scared her.

452
00:33:46,773 --> 00:33:49,883
Ma Ri! Ma Ri!

453
00:33:49,883 --> 00:33:52,133
 Ma Ri! 

454
00:33:52,133 --> 00:33:54,973
Ma Ri, hold on! Ma Ri.

455
00:33:54,973 --> 00:33:58,123
Gosh, Ma Ri.

456
00:33:58,123 --> 00:34:01,823
I'm so sorry I didn't keep the promise.

457
00:34:01,823 --> 00:34:05,733
But your mom indeed did the wrong thing.

458
00:34:05,733 --> 00:34:09,953
She abandoned Pil Sung in front of our house when he was a baby.

459
00:34:09,953 --> 00:34:13,683
And she kept frequenting our house, acting innocent.

460
00:34:15,113 --> 00:34:20,583
Ma Ri, imagine your close friend lied to you.

461
00:34:20,583 --> 00:34:23,823
Imagine how much you'd feel betrayed and angry.

462
00:34:23,823 --> 00:34:30,933
Pil Sung's mom has been lied to by your mom for 34 years.

463
00:34:30,933 --> 00:34:35,143
So, even if my daughter-in-law plucked all of your mom's hair,

464
00:34:35,143 --> 00:34:38,453
she won't be able to blame her for it.

465
00:34:38,453 --> 00:34:42,713
- You know that, right? 
 - Yes. I do, Grandma.

466
00:34:42,713 --> 00:34:44,133
Take care.

467
00:34:44,133 --> 00:34:45,863
Ma Ri.

468
00:34:46,483 --> 00:34:48,073
Hey.

469
00:34:50,243 --> 00:34:51,853
Gosh, seriously.

470
00:34:51,853 --> 00:34:54,093
What's going on?

471
00:34:54,093 --> 00:34:57,323
This is so upsetting.

472
00:35:00,923 --> 00:35:03,003
Honey, I'm home.

473
00:35:05,153 --> 00:35:07,023
Are you feeling sick?

474
00:35:08,183 --> 00:35:10,303
It's nothing.

475
00:35:10,303 --> 00:35:13,023
I'm just tired.

476
00:35:13,023 --> 00:35:16,173
Take a shower and have dinner.

477
00:35:16,173 --> 00:35:20,523
I came home from work, but you won't even let me see your face?

478
00:35:20,523 --> 00:35:22,753
What's with you?

479
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:25,753
Are you angry with me about something?

480
00:35:29,113 --> 00:35:32,053
Honey, what happened to your face?

481
00:35:32,923 --> 00:35:34,923
Did something happen?

482
00:35:35,943 --> 00:35:38,183
It's nothing.

483
00:35:41,193 --> 00:35:44,013
Chairman Gong, come out for a second.

484
00:35:44,833 --> 00:35:47,113
What did you say?

485
00:35:47,113 --> 00:35:50,463
Seon Yeong grabbed her by her hair?

486
00:35:50,463 --> 00:35:52,043
In front of our house, even?

487
00:35:52,043 --> 00:35:57,223
Yes, it wasn't just Seon Yeong. Her mother-in-law, too.

488
00:35:59,393 --> 00:36:00,963
Why?

489
00:36:00,963 --> 00:36:03,813
We want to know, too, but she won't tell us.

490
00:36:03,813 --> 00:36:08,923
But considering the circumstances, Soo Yeon must've done something terribly wrong.

491
00:36:08,923 --> 00:36:10,953
But still.

492
00:36:10,953 --> 00:36:14,413
What could she have done to yank her hair like that?

493
00:36:14,413 --> 00:36:16,513
They could've just talked it out.

494
00:36:16,513 --> 00:36:19,993
Everyone knows we're the APP Group's chairman's family.

495
00:36:19,993 --> 00:36:24,233
What if someone saw her getting beaten?

496
00:36:24,233 --> 00:36:28,263
I heard they beat her up like she was an adulterer or something.

497
00:36:28,263 --> 00:36:32,403
What if a false rumor like that ends up spreading?

498
00:36:32,403 --> 00:36:36,173
Auntie, how could you say that?

499
00:36:36,173 --> 00:36:37,983
Hold on.

500
00:36:41,223 --> 00:36:44,723
Honey, sit up straight.

501
00:36:52,583 --> 00:36:55,123
Is that all true?

502
00:36:55,123 --> 00:36:58,193
Seon Yeong and her mother-in-law did this?

503
00:36:58,193 --> 00:37:01,543
I'm asking if they did that to your face.

504
00:37:03,193 --> 00:37:05,683
There was a reason for it.

505
00:37:06,223 --> 00:37:08,923
So, you should just play ignorant.

506
00:37:08,923 --> 00:37:14,373
Even if there were a reason for it, how am I supposed to just ignore this?

507
00:37:14,373 --> 00:37:16,233
Honey,

508
00:37:17,233 --> 00:37:19,243
I...

509
00:37:20,953 --> 00:37:23,133
did something bad to Seon Yeong.

510
00:37:23,133 --> 00:37:26,533
So, please don't do anything.

511
00:37:26,533 --> 00:37:30,703
Please just play ignorant.

512
00:37:31,553 --> 00:37:34,063
What did you do wrong, exactly?

513
00:37:34,063 --> 00:37:37,463
Honey, just tell me. Tell me.

514
00:37:38,183 --> 00:37:41,813
Yes, Seon Yeong. Tell us.

515
